<Author>BockTheRobber
<Content>Pension 45 - A Grim Hovel If you want a night's sleep in this hotel, make sure to get blind drunk. Otherwise, either the noise in the street will keep you awake, or the owner's dog, barking all night in reception, will do the trick.Don't complain to the proprietor about his dog though, unless you can converse in fluent Spanish. He won't speak a word of English to you, and even the normal courtesies are not high on his agenda. He demanded a euro from me for calling a taxi, which I know is not a lot, but indicates the contempt this establishment has for its customers.If you want a shower, buy your own towel. The handkerchief-sized specimens supplied wouldn't dry a small mouse. Oh, and watch out for the shower head. It's inclined to fall off the wall without warning. Never was the expression dirt cheap more appropriate.Can I think of any positive points?Yes. You can always check out of this hotel and go somewhere decent. 
