<Content>the best accomodation in Barcellona? I got it: pension 45 and its staff! I'm an italian girl and I was in Barcellona this summer for the first time with a friend of mine.I arrived in Barcellona just with my baggage and without reservation. I looked for a room and I was in a lot of hostels but finally I chosed one: Pension 45, the best I found in Barcellona!It is located in a strategical place: you can reach rambla in just 2 minutes by walking and plaza catalunya in maybe 3 minutes.The hostel is very clean and at the price of 25euro for person in a double you have included breakfast too (Abdel prepare a wonderful napoletan coff猫!) until 12 in the morning. The most important aspect as regard as the hostel is its staff: the receptionist man is the best of all the world: friendly, fanny, and very serious!I will never forget barcelona, pension 45 and the staff of the pension of course.Thank you A. E.! 
